race.comment: MISHANI SUSPECT (5) impressed winning a CL1 at Ballina and then didn't have the best of it there in even stronger. Peaks today with a handy 1.5kg claim and maps well. She's well placed to bounce back. IT'SALLSAIDANDONE (6) has been out of the money twice since her easy all-the-way win at Coffs Harbour at this level. She's likely to sit handier today and if she puts her best foot forward, she's a quinella hope. NEOCLASSICISM (2) resumes and has won fresh. He's been racing on the Gold Coast poly and has pieces of form that stack up. Has a 2kg claim and will get every chance from an inside barrier. MISHANI BREEZE (12) has an awkward gate but has been within range her last two and shouldn't be taken lightly. DOYLE (13) has been freshened off a near miss at the track. Improved the one before and has to be kept onside.
